        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} I spent the afternoon and evening working. On my way to A Space Cebu, I made a small detour to a food market called Lenders. This seems to be a wholesaler, but tourists can enter by showing their passport. It was somehow strange to see that so many people have to buy in large quantities and abundance, while just 50 meters away, others have to earn their living on the street by selling individual fruits or chewing gum to passing cars or at traffic lights - a life-threatening affair given the driving style here. </p>
        <p> Once in the office, everything was basically fine, but unfortunately, the internet connection wasn't so great. The internet connection in my accommodation worked much better. But I have that all to myself. </p>
        <p> Tonight there was also a meetup at A Space Cebu that I wanted to attend. A meetup is essentially a gathering of an interest group, and these are usually public and free of charge. There are many different ones distributed around the world. I myself often help my colleagues at kartenmacherei organize meetups, which are often about IT topics. </p>
