    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> Today was the first meeting of the WordPress Meetup Group in Cebu. At the beginning, everyone was supposed to briefly introduce themselves and share their IT/WordPress knowledge. I mentioned that my specialty is architecture and testing of web applications. I was promptly asked to participate in a discussion round, as unfortunately, an invited software architect didn't show up. The discussion was quite pleasant and, in some questions, went right into my specialty of testing availability, as well as topics like clean code and remote working. After the meetup, I talked to several software developers and even subtly advertised kartenmacherei as an employer. Three of them had knowledge that was more than interesting for us. Let's see if anyone applies. </p>
        <p> There really wasn't much else to do today. It was a working day. </p>
